-- Budimex, Rafako Shares May Move: Central European Equity Market Preview
-- Monika Rozlal
-- 2010-07-16T03:59:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/budimex-rafako-shares-may-move-central-european-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  
 Poland’s  WIG20 Index  gained 0.3 percent, the Czech  PX Index 
was little changed at 1,174.90 and Hungary’s  BUX Index  slid 0.3
percent.  
 Budimex SA  (BDX PW): The Polish unit of Ferrovial SA won a
250.8 million-zloty ($79.5 million) order to build a bridge near
the northern city of Kwidzyn. Budimex shares added 0.2 percent
to 90.4 zloty.  
 Rafako SA  (RFK PW): Shareholders of the Polish engineering
company approved a 2009 dividend payout of 0.3 zloty a share,
the company said in a regulatory statement. Rafako gained 1.5
percent to 12.94 zloty.  
